        "name": ", IAPEN",
        "role": "Secretary",
        "details": "Bhopal Chapter. The talk focused on the causes, symptoms, and increasing prevalence of PCOS, emphasizing the role of balanced nutrition, physical activity, and healthy lifestyle practices in managing hormonal health. The session was interactive and well-received, providing practical insights for prevention and management. The webinar benefited UG and PG students along with faculty members. Members/Participants Involved: Ms. Annapurna Bhatnagar (Resource Person), Faculty members, UG FND and PG FSN students. World Dietetics Day 2026- Webinar Date : 12th January 2026 Platform : Google meet Beneficiaries: 25 students and 5 faculty members Webinar was hosted by the chapter to commemorate World Dietetics Day on the topic “Role of nutrition in cancer care: From diagnosis to survivorship “ by Ms. Daveena Pinto, Clinical Nutritionist & IAPEN member ,Mangalore Institute of Oncology, Mangalore. The main objective of the session is to enhance the clinical knowledge of students and faculty regarding the critical impact of nutritional intervention throughout the cancer journey. The webinar focused on the nutritional assessment of the patient ,management of side-effects through diet to ensure complete recovery and also on long term dietary strategies to improve quality of life, regain strength and potentially reduce the risk of recurrence. Total of 25 students and 5 faculties benefitted from the program. The program successfully highlighted the indispensable role of dietitians in the multidisciplinary approach to cancer treatment. The program was conducted in association with the Department of Food Nutrition & Dietetics, Alva’s College (Autonomous), Moodbidri Name & Place of the Activity: World Food Day 2025 Celebration – Mount Rosary Charitable Trust, Mangaluru Date of the Event: 16th October 2025 Brief Description: The IAPEN Mangaluru Chapter, in collaboration with Alva’s FSN, organized a World Food Day 2025 celebration at Mount Rosary Charitable Trust, Mangaluru. The event aimed to promote nutritional awareness and community well-being among elderly residents. A nutritious Nutri Lunch was served to 135 beneficiaries, followed by an interactive nutrition education session focusing on healthy dietary practices and food sustainability. The program emphasized the importance of balanced nutrition and social responsibility in improving quality of life. Members/Participants Involved: Members of IAPEN Mangaluru Chapter and faculty and students from Alva’s FSN actively participated in the event. Collaboration: In collaboration with Alva’s FSN. The Women Conclave – Nurturer the Nurturer was held at VS Acharya Hall, Alvas College , bringing together over 800 beneficiaries from diverse backgrounds. The conclave served as a powerful platform dedicated to celebrating, educating, and empowering women at every stage of life. The event hosted eminent panellists from across the country , representing various fields. Each expert shared unique insights and real-life experiences, creating a rich and interconnected dialogue. The discussions provided an integrated, holistic approach to enhancing women’s health —from puberty through reproductive years and into menopause. Through knowledge-sharing, interaction, and collaborative learning, the conclave strengthened awareness and inspired women to prioritize their health while also equipping them with practical strategies to thrive as the nurturers of society. World Diabetes Day 2025 – Diet Camp Location: Alva’s Education Foundation – Transport Division Beneficiaries: 80 Transport Workers IAPEN India – Mangaluru Chapter in association with The Dept. of PG Studies in Food Science and Nutrition, organized a World Diabetes Day 2025 diet camp for the transport workers of Alva’s Education Foundation.The camp included height, weight, BMI, blood pressure and blood glucose assessments, followed by individual diet counselling . A total of 80 participants benefitted from the initiative."
